THE Emir of Zazzau, in Zaria, Kaduna State, Shehu Idris, yesterday, said Nigerians were suffering as a result of “palpable hardship” in the country. <img class="size-full wp-image-1238697 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Shehu-Idris.jpg?resize=640%2C354&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="354" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Shehu-Idris.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Shehu-Idris.jpg?resize=300%2C166&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Shehu-Idris.jpg?resize=768%2C424&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Shehu-Idris.jpg?resize=1024%2C566&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Shehu-Idris.jpg?resize=58%2C32&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Shehu-Idris.jpg?resize=260%2C144&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Shehu-Idris.jpg?resize=200%2C111&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Shehu-Idris.jpg?resize=560%2C309&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Shehu-Idris.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> While delivering his Sallah message at his palace in Zaria, the monarch said intervention was needed at both federal and state levels. He enjoined farmers and herders to coexist peacefully and avoid rumours that fuel crisis. According to him, “the suffering requires the attention and assistance of the governments at both federal and state levels. Similarly, we are urging our people to continue to promote peaceful coexistence. Fulani herdsmen and farmers should respect the interest of one another. People are also urged to avoid rumour mongering and give maximum cooperation to security agents. Don says almajiri system may lead to greater societal problems(Opens in a new browser tab) “Kaduna State, local governments and the House of Assembly should take measures that would bring about development in the areas of agriculture, animal husbandry and education. If these sectors are given necessary attention, they are capable of bringing about peaceful coexistence and the end effect is improvement in the lives of our people.” Vanguard